"v.见证，证实 【英】 v.见证，证实(to bear witness to: attest; prove) 【记】 test(验证，目击)+if y→见证 【例】 refuse to testify against a friend(拒绝做不利于 朋友的证词) 无 【记】test 考试，测验 是(水平,能力)的见证与证明，老师做见证人 【相关】attest 证明 testify (v.)  late 14c., ""give legal testimony, affirm the truth of, bear witness to;"" of things, c.1400, ""serve as evidence of,"" from Anglo-French testifier, from Latin testificari ""bear witness, show, demonstrate,"" also ""call to witness,"" from testis ""a witness"" (see testament) + root of facere ""to make"" (see factitious). Biblical sense of ""openly profess one's faith and devotion"" is attested from 1520s. Related: Testified; testifying; testification."
